# Cline Rules

## Available Skills

This project has three agent skills. Use them when the task matches.

### Feature Design

Trigger: User wants to plan or design a new feature before building it.
File: @.cline/skills/FEATURE_DESIGN.md

### Feature Coder

Trigger: User has an approved FDD and wants to implement it.
File: @.cline/skills/FEATURE_CODER.md

### Feature Auditor

Trigger: User wants a read-only code review of a built feature.
File: @.cline/skills/FEATURE_AUDITOR.md
**Hard constraint: this agent may never write, modify, or create any file.**

## General Rules

- Always read the relevant skill file before starting that type of task
- Never begin building a feature without an approved FDD from FEATURE_DESIGN
- Match existing codebase conventions — check before introducing new patterns

```

---

## How You'd Actually Use Them Day-to-Day

**Starting a feature:**
```

Let's build a session history page. Use @.cline/skills/FEATURE_DESIGN.md

```

**Building from the plan:**
```

Plan is approved. Build it using @.cline/skills/FEATURE_CODER.md and @docs/session-history-FDD.md

```

**Running an audit:**
```

Audit src/features/session-history using @.cline/skills/FEATURE_AUDITOR.md
